The other settlements in the municipal unit are Agios Panteleimonas (pop. 1,591), Kato Souli (2,142), Vranas (1,082), Avra (191), Vothon (177), Ano Souli (232), and Schinias (264).

== Points of interest ==
[[File:Marathon, the mound of the Plataeans.jpg|thumb|The ''Soros'', a burial mound ([[Marathon tumuli]]) to the fallen of the [[Battle of Marathon]]]]
* The ''Soros'', a [[tumulus]] (Greek '' Œ§œçŒºŒ≤ŒøœÇ, tymbos'', tomb), or burial mound, erected to the 192 Athenian fallen at the Battle of Marathon, is a feature of the coastal plain, now marked by a marble memorial [[stele]] and surrounded by a small park.&lt;ref&gt;Aerial photograph in John Boardman, Jasper Griffin and Oswyn Murray, ''Greece and the Hellenistic World'' (Oxford History of the Classical World) 1988, vol. I p. 34.&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Kato Souli Naval Transmission Facility]] with its {{convert|250|m|adj=on}} tall radio mast, the tallest structure in Greece.

